INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS.DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS:
Participação em projeto de cooperação com a Universidade de Karlsruhe, Alemanha.
Data: 10 de março.

Abstract:
In my talk I'll present possible-translations semantics (also known as non-deterministic semantics), a new logical tool based on translations between logical systems.
The idea is combining logics with well-known semantics so as to provide new semantics to non-classical logics, or even obtaining new logics, designed to meet specific needs.
Various practical examples will be presented:
-paraconsistent hierarchies and the calculi that limit their theories;
-paracomplete and dual logics;
-combination of copies of classical logic (society semantics);
-combination of modal systems.

